              "message": "D2 asks for a semantic rewrite of the post-merge roadmap ADR: it changes the Phase 3 decision's front-matter `status` to `superseded` and adds `superseded_by`. The pre-track ADR convention only allows post-merge edits for typos, broken cross-references, or adding a newer-ADR back-reference, so this supersession procedure is not executable as written. It needs to be represented as a new ADR/back-reference rather than a semantic edit to the merged roadmap ADR.",
