        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`GuideEntry` and `GuideMatch` are declared in the domain catalogue with `kind: \"dto\"`, but the type-designer kind-selection convention marks `dto` as forbidden for the domain layer, not a rationale-required exception. This makes the catalogue layer/kind classification semantically invalid even though the entries are deletion declarations.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/external-guides-removal-2026-04-28/domain-types.json",
              "line": 9,
              "category": "architecture violation"
            },
            {
              "message": "`ComplianceContext` is classified as a `value_object`, but the current domain type has behavior methods such as `render()` that compute the injected additionalContext string. The kind-selection convention restricts value objects to validated/read-only values and explicitly excludes behavior-bearing structs, so this catalogue entry misclassifies the domain type.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/external-guides-removal-2026-04-28/domain-types.json",
              "line": 39,
              "category": "architecture violation"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:d6ab2ecc2e4ea1d951ef8266751ff961e3dc86d74e6edd0f625484cac4e2eb5d",
          "at": "2026-04-28T17:09:25Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`GuideEntry` and `GuideMatch` are declared as `kind: \"dto\"` in the domain catalogue, but the current kind-selection convention marks `dto` in the domain layer as forbidden, not merely requiring rationale. The descriptions also say these structs have no serde derives, which conflicts with the convention's DTO rationale as an infrastructure serde-boundary type.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/external-guides-removal-2026-04-28/domain-types.json",
              "line": 9,
              "category": "architecture"
            },
            {
              "message": "`ComplianceContext` is classified as a `value_object`, but the convention restricts value objects to validated values and excludes behavior-bearing structs. This type is a skill compliance result/context with rendering/emptiness behavior and no stated validation invariant, so the catalogue kind conflicts with R3/R5.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/external-guides-removal-2026-04-28/domain-types.json",
              "line": 39,
              "category": "architecture"
            },
            {
              "message": "The `trigger_matches` catalogue entry records `expected_returns` as an empty list, but the deleted function is a predicate and returns `bool`. This makes the delete declaration factually inaccurate for the removed contract.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/external-guides-removal-2026-04-28/domain-types.json",
              "line": 145,
              "category": "factual_error"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:d6ab2ecc2e4ea1d951ef8266751ff961e3dc86d74e6edd0f625484cac4e2eb5d",
          "at": "2026-04-28T17:12:15Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`GuideEntry` and `GuideMatch` are declared as `kind: \"value_object\"` while their descriptions say they are plain data-carrier structs with no validation invariants. The type-designer convention defines `value_object` as a validated value and forbids using it as a catch-all, so these catalogue entries are semantically misclassified even though they are `action: delete`.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/external-guides-removal-2026-04-28/domain-types.json",
              "line": 6,
              "category": "factual error (semantic)"
            },
            {
              "message": "`ComplianceContext` is declared as a `value_object`, but the same description says it has no validation-on-construction invariant and it exposes `render()`, which computes formatted output rather than merely returning stored values. Under R3, value objects are limited to validated/read-only values and behavior like this should not be classified as `value_object`.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/external-guides-removal-2026-04-28/domain-types.json",
              "line": 36,
              "category": "factual error (semantic)"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:00d10cdbf9c08c8f4f1846bf0f2a84c04631e1b65667b10f79792d97ea28d878",
          "at": "2026-04-28T17:16:52Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "GuideEntry and GuideMatch are now classified as `value_object`, but the catalogue rationale describes them only as plain read-only data carriers with no validation behavior. The project kind convention restricts `value_object` to validated values, while the briefing says the accepted treatment for these deleted guide containers was the explicitly justified DTO classification. As written, the catalogue and generated views mis-state the semantic role of these domain types instead of documenting the approved deviation.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/external-guides-removal-2026-04-28/domain-types.json",
              "line": 9,
              "category": "factual error"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:1b99321d675ae68b41ca2b63cde40600b52ef751c6bb257fb1bf11b3d4cd84db",
          "at": "2026-04-28T17:20:52Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`ComplianceContext` is declared as `kind: \"value_object\"`, but the type still owns behavior (`is_empty()` and `render()` in the implementation). Under the R3 kind-selection rule, value objects are limited to validated/read-only values and accessors; rendering/computation behavior makes this catalogue declaration semantically wrong, so the type signal can be incorrectly Blue despite a kind mismatch.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/external-guides-removal-2026-04-28/domain-types.json",
              "line": 39,
              "category": "kind_selection"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:b664cca7c8e02215d8e280ea46f38e0b1788f366c3d03e13f71084af5528b257",
          "at": "2026-04-28T17:24:40Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`ComplianceContext` is approved as `kind: \"value_object\"` while the entry itself says this is an “accepted R3 deviation” and justifies it as a pragmatic fallback. The required kind-selection convention restricts `value_object` to validated values and R5 forbids using it as the fallback when no other kind fits; `render()` is behavior, not a value accessor. This catalogue entry therefore records a kind choice that contradicts the governing design convention and should be changed or escalated rather than approved as-is.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/external-guides-removal-2026-04-28/domain-types.json",
              "line": 36,
              "category": "contradiction"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:67968176532caec9a0db55ffb3d2ce6b13059cb64b18b96bad9aa48d53d5f679",
          "at": "2026-04-28T17:27:09Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`ComplianceContext` is declared as `kind: \"value_object\"` and the description claims its invariant is established at construction, but this catalog entry does not describe a validated constructor or read-only value boundary; the implementation shape is a result/context struct with behavior (`is_empty`/`render`). Under R3, `value_object` is limited to validated values and must not be used as a catch-all for behavior-bearing structs, so this catalogue declaration is semantically inconsistent unless it is reclassified or documented as an explicit accepted deviation.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/external-guides-removal-2026-04-28/domain-types.json",
              "line": 35,
              "category": "factual error"
            }
